   <mods:abstract>A general British and American legislature to regulate the administration
            of the general affairs of the colonies shall be set up. The colonies shall regulate all
            their internal affairs. Administration by a President General appointed by the King and
            a grand council chosen by the colonies. All colonies to be represented on council.
            Election every three years, and a meeting once a year. Council shall have all liberties
            of House of Commons. Assent of President General to all acts necessary. President and
            Council have all legislative power over all general commercial and criminal matters, and
            are an inferior and distinct branch of Parliament whose assent is necessary to the
            validity of all acts. In time of war all bills for aid to the Crown will not need
            Parliamentary assent.</mods:abstract>
